title: Chinese tennis star tells officials she is safe
content: Peng Shuai disappeared from the public eye after making sex assault allegations against a Chinese minister.

title: More protests erupt in Europe over Covid curbs
content: Belgium says 35,000 took part in protests, with unrest in the Netherlands, Austria and Italy.

title: Gunman kills one and injures three in Jerusalem
content: A member of the Hamas militant group opens fire in the Old City, and is shot dead by Israeli police.

title: Taliban bans women from TV dramas in Afghanistan
content: The Islamist group unveils new rules including ordering female TV presenters to wear headscarves.

title: Sudan's military reinstates ousted civilian PM
content: Abdalla Hamdok's release from house arrest fails to stop protests against the army's political role.

title: Haiti kidnappers release two missionary hostages
content: Two people among a group of 17 US and Canadian missionaries abducted last month are said to be safe.

title: El Salvador plans Bitcoin city at base of volcano
content: Funded by the cryptocurrency, it will use the volcano's energy to power mining, the president says.
